***********************************************************************************************************************************

PART 1: BLAST

The first available option for using the DIGIT tool is to perform a BLAST search of the flanking sequence fasta file against the 3
standard maize genomes, A188v1, B73v5, and W22v2. This step must be completed in order to find any further primer data. BLAST out-
put arrives as a .tab file that will appear in DIGITfiles/BlastOutput/<flankseq>/ . There will be 3 files, one for each of the
maize genomes listed before.

To use this feature, simply follow the prompts given by the program when running. Be sure to select the correct flanking sequence
fasta file.

***********************************************************************************************************************************

